---
// src/pages/rules/keywords.astro
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Keywords & Abilities"
  description="All Alt-Hammer 40,000 universal keywords and wargear abilities — cross-linked reference."
  activePage="rules"
  sidebarType="rules"
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="/rules/core-rules">Core Rules</a></p>
    <h1>Keywords &amp; Abilities</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      All universal model type keywords and wargear ability keywords, with full rules text.
      Keywords appearing in bold small-caps throughout the rules link back to this page.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section id="model-characteristics">
    <h2>Model Characteristics</h2>
    <p>Every model in Alt-Hammer has the following characteristics on its datasheet:</p>
    <div class="data-table-wrap">
      <table class="data-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Abbrev.</th>
            <th style="text-align:left;">Characteristic</th>
            <th style="text-align:left;">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {[
            ['M',  'Movement',         'Maximum distance in inches the model can move per Move Action.'],
            ['WS', 'Weapon Skill',      'Proficiency with melee weapons — used as attacker and defender in Hit Roll Table.'],
            ['BS', 'Ballistic Skill',   'Proficiency with ranged weapons — used as attacker and defender in Hit Roll Table.'],
            ['I',  'Initiative',        'Determines fight order in simultaneous combat situations.'],
            ['A',  'Attacks',           'Number of attack dice the model rolls per weapon when fighting.'],
            ['S',  'Strength',          'Physical power of the model — compared against target Toughness in Wound Roll Table.'],
            ['T',  'Toughness',         'Resilience of the model — compared against attacker Strength in Wound Roll Table.'],
            ['W',  'Wounds',            'Number of wounds the model can suffer before being destroyed.'],
            ['SV', 'Armour Save',       'D6 roll required to avoid a wound after a failed save (lower is better, e.g. 3+ beats 4+).'],
            ['LD', 'Leadership',        'D6 roll required to pass Battle Shock and Rally checks.'],
            ['OC', 'Objective Control', 'Contributes to controlling Primary Objective Markers.'],
          ].map(([abbr, name, desc]) => (
            <tr>
              <td style="font-family:var(--font-mono);color:var(--color-gold);font-weight:700;">{abbr}</td>
              <td class="row-header">{name}</td>
              <td style="text-align:left;font-family:var(--font-body);color:var(--color-text-secondary);">{desc}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="core-model-type-keywords">
    <h2>Core Model Type Keywords</h2>
    <p>
      Every model in Alt-Hammer belongs to exactly one Core Model Type. This keyword governs
      fundamental interactions with terrain, actions, and special rules.
    </p>

    <h3 id="infantry">Infantry</h3>
    <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-style:italic;">
      [ Paste Infantry keyword rules from Core Rules here. ]
    </p>

    <h3 id="vehicle">Vehicle</h3>
    <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-style:italic;">
      [ Paste Vehicle keyword rules from Core Rules here. ]
    </p>

    <h3 id="monster">Monster</h3>
    <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-style:italic;">
      [ Paste Monster keyword rules from Core Rules here. ]
    </p>

    <h3 id="beast">Beast</h3>
    <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-style:italic;">
      [ Paste Beast keyword rules from Core Rules here. ]
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="additional-model-keywords">
    <h2>Additional Model Type Keywords</h2>

    <h3 id="battleline">Battleline</h3>
    <p>
      Up to 2 of each unit with the <span class="keyword">Battleline</span> keyword can be
      taken for every 500 points. Battleline units are eligible to make Bonus Activations,
      and often have interactions with faction Army Rules.
    </p>

    <h3 id="character">Character</h3>
    <p>
      Up to 1 of each unit with the <span class="keyword">Character</span> keyword can be
      taken for every 1,000 points.
    </p>
    <p>
      Models with the <span class="keyword">Character</span> keyword can only be selected
      as the subject of an attack under the following conditions:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>The model is the closest model to the attacking unit when making a Ranged attack, and is not within 3" of any other friendly units.</li>
      <li>The model is in base-to-base contact with the attacking model when making a Melee attack.</li>
      <li>The attacking model has the <span class="keyword">Precision</span> ability.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      These conditions do not apply to <span class="keyword">Character</span> units that also
      possess <span class="keyword">Vehicle</span> or <span class="keyword">Monster</span> keywords.
    </p>

    <h3 id="leader">Leader</h3>
    <p>
      Models with the <span class="keyword">Leader</span> keyword can choose to lead a friendly
      Unit. Eligible units are listed on the Leader's Unit Profile. Leader models and their
      attached unit count as a single unit for Activation purposes and when targeted by attacks.
      Leader/unit attachment is declared during Pregame Setup.
    </p>

    <h3 id="deep-strike">Deep Strike</h3>
    <p>
      Units where every model has the <span class="keyword">Deep Strike</span> keyword can use
      the <em>Enter the Battlefield from Strategic Reserve</em> action, and can be placed anywhere
      on the battlefield that is at least 9" horizontally and/or vertically from any enemy units.
    </p>

    <h3 id="infiltrator">Infiltrator</h3>
    <p>
      Units where every model has the <span class="keyword">Infiltrator</span> keyword can be
      set up anywhere in No Man's Land that is at least 9" horizontally from the edge of the
      enemy deployment zone and at least 9" from any other enemy units already deployed using
      this ability. Additionally, these models ignore Movement modifiers when moving through
      Light Cover or Heavy Cover terrain.
    </p>

    <h3 id="scout">Scout [X]"</h3>
    <p>
      Units where every model has the <span class="keyword">Scout [X]"</span> keyword can
      complete a Normal Move of up to X" before the start of the Activation Phase in Battle
      Round 1. The Initiative player resolves first, then players alternate.
    </p>

    <h3 id="titanic">Titanic</h3>
    <p>
      Models with the <span class="keyword">Titanic</span> keyword:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Cannot benefit from Light Cover or Heavy Cover.</li>
      <li>Cannot benefit from the Obscuring keyword while any part of the model is visible.</li>
      <li>Can move through terrain features (except Impassable), reducing Movement by 4". After moving through, replace that feature with Difficult Ground only (unless it has the Hill keyword).</li>
      <li>Can move over enemy and friendly models. Roll 1D6 for each model passed over or ended in base contact with — on a 5+, that model suffers a Mortal Wound.</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-style:italic;">
      [ Additional model type keywords — Walker, Mounted, Swarm, Psyker, Small Profile, Phase Shift, Hover, Jump Pack, Fly, Aircraft, Bodyguard, Unyielding, Relentless, Stealth — paste here from Core Rules document following the same pattern. ]
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="armour-save-abilities">
    <h2>Armour Save Abilities</h2>

    <h3 id="invulnerable-save">Invulnerable Save [X]+</h3>
    <p>
      Models with the <span class="keyword">Invulnerable Save [X]+</span> ability may use
      this save instead of their standard Armour Save. The invulnerable save is never
      modified by a weapon's AP characteristic.
    </p>

    <h3 id="feel-no-pain">Feel No Pain [X]+</h3>
    <p>
      Each time this model would lose a wound (including from Mortal Wounds), roll 1D6.
      On a result equal to or greater than X, that wound is not lost.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="wargear-abilities">
    <h2>Wargear Abilities</h2>
    <p>
      The following abilities appear on weapon profiles in the Faction Data Tables.
      All wargear abilities are universal — they work identically regardless of which
      faction uses them.
    </p>

    <h3 id="assault">Assault</h3>
    <p>This weapon can be used to make Ranged attacks even if the bearer's unit has Advanced this turn.</p>

    <h3 id="heavy">Heavy</h3>
    <p>
      If the bearer's unit has moved this turn (other than Remaining Stationary), subtract 1
      from Hit rolls made with this weapon.
    </p>

    <h3 id="rapid-fire">Rapid Fire [X]</h3>
    <p>
      Each time an attack is made with this weapon against a target within half of its
      maximum range, increase the Attacks characteristic by X for that attack.
    </p>

    <h3 id="sustained-hits">Sustained Hits [X]</h3>
    <p>
      Each time a Critical Hit is scored with this weapon, it scores X additional hits
      on the target.
    </p>

    <h3 id="devastating-wounds">Devastating Wounds</h3>
    <p>
      Each time a Critical Wound is scored with this weapon, the target cannot make any
      Armour Save or Invulnerable Save against it. Instead, the attack inflicts Mortal
      Wounds equal to the weapon's Damage characteristic.
    </p>

    <h3 id="lethal-hits">Lethal Hits</h3>
    <p>Each time a Critical Hit is scored with this weapon, it automatically wounds the target — no Wound roll required.</p>

    <h3 id="precision">Precision</h3>
    <p>
      When this weapon successfully wounds an Attached unit, the attacking player may allocate
      the attack to a visible Character model in that unit instead of following the normal
      attack sequence.
    </p>

    <h3 id="torrent">Torrent</h3>
    <p>Attacks made with this weapon automatically hit — no Hit roll required.</p>

    <h3 id="melta">Melta [X]</h3>
    <p>
      Each time an attack is made with this weapon against a target within half of its
      maximum range, add X to the Damage roll for that attack (if the Damage characteristic
      is a fixed number, treat it as a roll result of that number before adding X).
    </p>

    <h3 id="twin-linked">Twin-Linked</h3>
    <p>
      The <span class="keyword">Twin-Linked</span> ability modifies a weapon's profile as follows:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Increase the Attacks characteristic by 1.</li>
      <li>Grants <span class="keyword">Sustained Hits 1</span>, or increases an existing <span class="keyword">Sustained Hits [X]</span> value by 1.</li>
      <li>If the weapon cannot have Sustained Hits (e.g. has Torrent), the Attacks characteristic is increased by 3 instead.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This ability is not found on base weapon profiles — it is added through Faction Wargear Upgrades.</p>

    <h3 id="smoke">Smoke [X]"</h3>
    <p>
      Place a 25mm marker anywhere within range and line of sight. This marker persists until
      the end of the Battle Round. Units drawing line of sight within X" of the marker reduce
      their BS to 2. Models within X" of the marker reduce their Initiative by 2 when completing
      Charge and Fight, and reduce their Hit rolls by 1 when fighting.
    </p>

    <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-style:italic;">
      [ Additional wargear abilities — Anti-[KEYWORD] [X+], Blast, Grenade, Ensnare, Haywire,
      Extra Attacks, Indirect Fire, Ignores Cover, Pistol, Lance, etc. — paste here from
      Core Rules document. ]
    </p>
  </section>

</DocsLayout>
